    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "war liend\nShip\nBoeing Model 727-200-\nCollector Series\nUminted\ntor Ano",
      "Boeing Model 727-200-\nsengers, was stretched 20 to complete tae\nto complete the\n727-200, with a capacity of 189. This aircraft\nwas first available to airlines in\n1967. By the\nend of 1970 the 727 had become the world's\nlargest-selling jet airliner. Length: 153'2\". Wing-\nspan: 108'. Cruising speed: 600 mph.\nCopyright 1973 by Johns-Byrne Co., Chicago, III.\nPLACE\nSTAMP\nHERE\nSpecial Offer\nPrints of this art available 9\" x 12\", ready to frame. Send $2.00 check or money order for each print to: Johns-Byrne Co., 161 W. Harrison, Chicago, III. 60605.\nPlease specify type of aircraft (727-200). Complete list of other available aircraft prints will be sent to you with your order. Allow three weeks for delivery.\n833473"
    ],
